In my opinion, you could publish it in 3 available clash modes

Please apply the formatting correctly and use consistent variable names:
* Goal section: You may format '(' and ')' as {{constants}} and remove the quotation marks.
* Input section: Use the same variable name as the stub generator, so please state "a string [[log]]" instead of "a [[string]]".
* Output section: Use the same variable name as the stub generator, so please state "an integer [[floor]]" instead of "a [[int]]". (Note the article "an" and use the full form "integer" as well.)
* Constraints section: Similar to above, please state "length of [[log]]" instead of "[[input.length]]".

You may also remove the redundant "Input : " and "Output : " in the descriptions.

Goal section
* Please specify that the elevator starts on Floor {{0}} and there is no limit to the number of floors in both up (positive) and down (negative) directions.

Thanks.
